Write an SQL query 

Problem Statement:
Find the top 3 employees in each region based on their total sales.

Table Schema: Emp

| Column Name       | Data Type | Description                           |
| ----------------- | --------- | ------------------------------------- |
| EmpName           | VARCHAR   | Name of the employee                  |
| Region            | VARCHAR   | Region of the employee                |
| Sales             | INT       | Sales amount for a transaction        |

Sample Input

| EmpName    | Region     | Sales     | 
| ---------- | ---------- | --------- |
| Hitesh     | East       | 100       |
| Hitesh     | East       | 300       |
| Ramesh     | West       | 100       |
| Suresh     | East       | 200       |
| Mahesh     | East       | 150       |
| Rajesh     | East       | 250       |

Write an SQL query to find the top 3 employees in each region based on their total sales.

Each employee may have multiple transactions. You need to:

1) Calculate the total sales per employee per region
2) Rank employees within each region based on total sales (highest first)
3) Return only the top 3 employees from each region

Expected Output

| EmpName    | Region     | total_sales     | 
| ---------- | ---------- | --------------- |
| Hitesh     | East       | 400             |
| Rajesh     | East       | 250             |
| Suresh     | East       | 200             |
| Ramesh     | West       | 100             |

Solution (Using Window Function)

WITH emp_sales AS (
    SELECT 
        EmpName,
        Region,
        SUM(Sales) AS total_sales
    FROM Emp
    GROUP BY EmpName, Region
),
ranked AS (
    SELECT *,
           RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY Region ORDER BY total_sales DESC) AS rnk
    FROM emp_sales
)
SELECT EmpName, Region, total_sales
FROM ranked
WHERE rnk <= 3;
